ciscoWan3gMIB.name: ciscoWan3gMIB

revisions.description: Modified Description of the ciscoWan3gMIB module. Modified the description of c3gWanCommonTable, c3gWanLbsCommonTable, c3gSmsCommonTable and all its objects to emphazise that it is technology independent. Added enumerated value lte to objects C3gServiceCapability, c3gCurrentIdleDigitalMode, c3gGsmPacketService. Modified the descriptions of c3gGsmIdentityTable, and all its objects to emphazise that these objects are applicable to both 3G and 4G-LTE Technology. Added new object c3gGpsState to the table c3gWanCommonTable. Added enumerated value lteBand for c3gGsmCurrentBand. Modified ciscoWan3gMIBGsmObjectGroup, ciscoWan3gMIBSmsObjectGroup, ciscoWan3gMIBLbsObjectGroup, ciscoWan3gMIBGsmObjectGroup description in Module ciscoWan3gMIBCompliance, ciscoWan3gMIBCompliance1. Added c3gGpsState to the group ciscoWan3gMIBCommonObjectGroup.
Added enumerated values rate56kbps(12) to rate8dot4mbps(18) for C3gUmtsQosLinkBitRate.
Added c3gWanLbs and c3gWanSms. Added ciscoWan3gMIBSmsObjectGroup and ciscoWan3gMIBSmsObjectGroup. Deprecated ciscoWan3gMIBCompliance and replaced by ciscoWan3gMIBCompliance1.
Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoWan3gMIB.description: This MIB module provides network management support for Cisco cellular 3G and 4G LTE WAN products. *** ABBREVIATIONS, ACRONYMS, AND SYMBOLS *** 1xRTT - 1 times Radio Transmission Technology. 3G - Third generation of mobile phones standards and technologies. 4G - Fourth generation of mobile phones standards and technologies Azimuth - Angle of rotation of a satellite Dish. BER - Bit Error Ratio. BS - Base Station. CDMA - Code Division Multiple Access. dB - decibel. dBm - power ratio in decibels (dB) of the measured power referenced to one milliwatt (mW). CnS - Control and Status proprietary protocol for managing the control and status of the modem. Ec/Io - ratio of received pilot energy, Ec, to total received energy or the total power spectral density, Io. EDGE - Enhanced Data rate for GSM Evolution. EPS - Evolved Packet System EVDO - EVolution Data Optimized. FDD - Frequency Division Duplexing GPRS - General Packet Radio Service. GSM - Global System for Mobile communications. GPS - Global Positioning System. HSDPA - High Speed Downlink Packet Access. HSPA - High Speed Packet Access. HSUPA - High Speed Uplink Packet Access. LBS - Location Based Service. LTE - Long Term Evolution MT - Mobile Termination. PDP - Packet Data Protocol. PLMN - Public Land Mobile Network. QoS - Quality of Service. RSSI - Received Signal Strength Indication. SDU - Service Data Unit. SER - SDU Error Ratio. SIM - Subscriber Identity Module. SMS - Short Messaging Service. SNR - Signal to Noise Ratio. TDD - Time Division Duplexing UMTS - Universal Mobile Telecommunication System. WCDMA - Wideband Code Division Multiple Access.

c3gNotifRadioService.name: c3gNotifRadioService
c3gNotifRadioService.description: This object is used as one of the var-bind object when notification for RSSI or Ec/Io is generated. This object indicates which service generates the notification.

c3gNotifRssi.name: c3gNotifRssi
c3gNotifRssi.description: This object is used as one of the var-bind object when notification for RSSI is generated. The relevant RSSI will be copied into c3gNotifRssi which corresponds to the service indicated in c3gNotifRadioService object. This object will reflect the value of one of the following objects: c3gCurrent1xRttRssi, c3gCurrentEvDoRssi and c3gCurrentGsmRssi. User should not use this object to get the current RSSI value as this object is used to indicate the RSSI value that triggers c3gRssiOnsetNotif or c3gRssiAbateNotif notification.

c3gNotifEcIo.name: c3gNotifEcIo
c3gNotifEcIo.description: This object is used as one of the var-bind object when notification for Ec/Io is generated. The relevant Ec/Io will be copied into c3gNotifEcIo which corresponds to the service indicated in c3gNotifRadioService object. This object will reflect the value of one of the following objects: c3gCurrent1xRttEcIo, c3gCurrentEvDoEcIo and c3gCurrentGsmEcIo. User should not use this object to get the current Ec/Io value as this object is used to indicate the Ec/Io value that triggers c3gEcIoOnsetNotif or c3gEcIoAbateNotif notification.

c3gRssiOnsetNotifThreshold.name: c3gRssiOnsetNotifThreshold
c3gRssiOnsetNotifThreshold.description: The RSSI onset threshold value. If RSSI goes below the threshold and the service bit in c3gRssiOnsetNotifFlag is set, the c3gRssiOnsetNotif notification for that service will be sent. The absolute value of c3gRssiAbateNotifThreshold should be less than or equal to the absolute value of c3gRssiOnsetNotifThreshold (|c3gRssiAbateNotifThreshold| <= |c3gRssiOnsetNotifThreshold|). e.g. setting c3gRssiAbateNotifThreshold to -115 dBm and then setting c3gRssiOnsetNotifThreshold to -110 dBm is not allowed and will be rejected.

c3gRssiAbateNotifThreshold.name: c3gRssiAbateNotifThreshold
c3gRssiAbateNotifThreshold.description: The RSSI abate threshold value. If RSSI goes above the threshold and the service bit in c3gRssiAbateNotifFlag is set, the c3gRssiAbateNotif notification for that service will be sent. The absolute value of c3gRssiAbateNotifThreshold should be less than or equal to the absolute value of c3gRssiOnsetNotifThreshold (|c3gRssiAbateNotifThreshold| <= |c3gRssiOnsetNotifThreshold|). e.g. setting c3gRssiAbateNotifThreshold to -115 dBm and then setting c3gRssiOnsetNotifThreshold to -110 dBm is not allowed and will be rejected.

c3gEcIoOnsetNotifThreshold.name: c3gEcIoOnsetNotifThreshold
c3gEcIoOnsetNotifThreshold.description: The EcIo onset threshold value. If EcIo goes below the threshold and the service bit in c3gEcIoOnsetNotifFlag is set, the c3gEcIoOnsetNotif notification for that service will be sent. The absolute value of c3gEcIoAbateNotifThreshold should be less than or equal to the absolute value of c3gEcIoOnsetNotifThreshold (|c3gEcIoAbateNotifThreshold| <= |c3gEcIoOnsetNotifThreshold|). e.g. setting c3gEcIoAbateNotifThreshold to -15 dB and then setting c3gEcIoOnsetNotifThreshold to -10 dB is not allowed and will be rejected.

c3gEcIoAbateNotifThreshold.name: c3gEcIoAbateNotifThreshold
c3gEcIoAbateNotifThreshold.description: The threshold value that if EcIo goes above the threshold and the service bit in c3gEcIoAbateNotifFlag is set, the c3gEcIoAbateNotif notification for that service will be sent. The absolute value of c3gEcIoAbateNotifThreshold should be less than or equal to the absolute value of c3gEcIoOnsetNotifThreshold (|c3gEcIoAbateNotifThreshold| <= |c3gEcIoOnsetNotifThreshold|). e.g. setting c3gEcIoOnsetNotifThreshold to -15 dB and then setting c3gEcIoAbateNotifThreshold to -10 dB is not allowed and will be rejected.

c3gModemTemperOnsetNotifThreshold.name: c3gModemTemperOnsetNotifThreshold
c3gModemTemperOnsetNotifThreshold.description: The modem temperature onset threshold value. If modem temperature goes above the threshold and the value of c3gModemTemperOnsetNotifEnabled is 'true', the c3gModemTemperOnsetNotif notification will be sent. The value of c3gModemTemperAbateNotifThreshold should be less than or equal to the value of c3gModemTemperOnsetNotifThreshold. e.g. setting c3gModemTemperAbateNotifThreshold to 50 degree Celsius and then setting c3gModemTemperOnsetNotifThreshold to 40 degree Celsius is not allowed and will be rejected.

c3gModemTemperAbateNotifThreshold.name: c3gModemTemperAbateNotifThreshold
c3gModemTemperAbateNotifThreshold.description: The modem temperature abate threshold value. If modem temperature goes below the threshold and the value of c3gModemTemperAbateNotifEnabled is 'true', the c3gModemTemperAbateNotif notification will be sent. The value of c3gModemTemperAbateNotifThreshold should be less than or equal to the value of c3gModemTemperOnsetNotifThreshold. e.g. setting c3gModemTemperAbateNotifThreshold to 50 degree Celsius and then setting c3gModemTemperOnsetNotifThreshold to 40 degree Celsius is not allowed and will be rejected.

c3gModemDownNotifEnabled.name: c3gModemDownNotifEnabled

c3gConnectionStatusChangedNotifFlag.name: c3gConnectionStatusChangedNotifFlag

The default value of this object is '00'H.

c3gRssiOnsetNotifFlag.description: This object is the flag bitmap to control the generation of notification c3gRssiOnsetNotif. Each bit represents a service as defined in C3gServiceCapability, set the bit value to 1 to enable (and 0 to disable) the generation of notification c3gRssiOnsetNotif for that service. The default value of this object is all bits are 0.

c3gRssiAbateNotifFlag.name: c3gRssiAbateNotifFlag

Each bit represents a service as defined in C3gServiceCapability, set the bit value to 1 to enable (and 0 to disable) the generation of notification c3gRssiAbateNotif for that service. The default value of this object is all bits are 0.

c3gEcIoOnsetNotifFlag.name: c3gEcIoOnsetNotifFlag
c3gEcIoOnsetNotifFlag.description: This object is the flag bitmap to control the generation of notification c3gEcIoOnsetNotif. Each bit represents a service as defined in C3gServiceCapability, set the bit value to 1 to enable (and 0 to disable) the generation of notification c3gEcIoOnsetNotif for that service. The default value of this object is all bits are 0.

c3gEcIoAbateNotifFlag.name: c3gEcIoAbateNotifFlag
c3gEcIoAbateNotifFlag.description: This object is the flag bitmap to control the generation of notification c3gEcIoAbateNotif. Each bit represents a service as defined in C3gServiceCapability, set the bit value to 1 to enable (and 0 to disable) the generation of notification c3gEcIoAbateNotif for that service. The default value of this object is all bits are 0.

c3gModemTemperOnsetNotifEnabled.description: This object is used to enable/disable the generation of c3gModemTemperOnsetNotif notification.

c3gModemTemperAbateNotifEnabled.name: c3gModemTemperAbateNotifEnabled
c3gModemTemperAbateNotifEnabled.description: This object is used to enable/disable the generation of c3gModemTemperAbateNotif notification.

c3gGpsState.name: c3gGpsState

c3gCdmaSessionTable.name: c3gCdmaSessionTable
c3gCdmaSessionTable.description: This table describes wireless session (link) created when a modem connects to a particular cellular network. One or more logical calls can be placed over wireless session(link). These logical calls are represented in the c3gCdmaConnectionTable.

c3gCdmaSessionEntry.name: c3gCdmaSessionEntry
c3gCdmaSessionEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the c3gCdmaSessionTable.

c3gCdmaTotalTransmitted.name: c3gCdmaTotalTransmitted
c3gCdmaTotalTransmitted.description: Total data transmitted for all calls. It is the total amount of data transmitted by modem, not to be confused with the number of bytes transmitted through the interface.

c3gCdmaTotalReceived.name: c3gCdmaTotalReceived
c3gCdmaTotalReceived.description: Total data received for all calls. It is the total amount of data received by modem, not to be confused with the number of bytes received from the interface.

c3gHdrDdtmPreference.name: c3gHdrDdtmPreference

c3gCdmaConnectionTable.name: c3gCdmaConnectionTable
c3gCdmaConnectionTable.description: Cellular 3G CDMA connection table. This table describes logical connections/calls over wireless link, the wireless link is described in c3gCdmaSessionTable.

c3gCdmaConnectionEntry.name: c3gCdmaConnectionEntry
c3gCdmaConnectionEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the c3gCdmaConnectionTable.

c3gHdrAtState.name: c3gHdrAtState

c3gUati.name: c3gUati
c3gUati.description: Unicast Access Terminal Identifier (UATI), AT seeking access to the 1 times EV-DO system receives a UATI allocated from the system after setting up a radio traffic channel with a base station.

c3gColorCode.name: c3gColorCode
c3gColorCode.description: Color code. A sync channel may be used by the base station to communicate administrative information to a mobile station. For example, a base station may transmit a base station ID to a user, a color code and administrative information identifying system status.

c3gRati.name: c3gRati
c3gRati.description: Random Access Terminal Identifier (RATI). AT transmits a UATI request message to the ANC using the RATI to make a UATI allocation request.

c3gHdrSessionDuration.name: c3gHdrSessionDuration
c3gHdrSessionDuration.description: HDR connection session duration. It is the duration between c3gHdrSessionStart and c3gHdrSessionEnd.

c3gAuthStatus.description: Connection authentication status: unknown(1) - authentication status is unknown notAuthenticated(2) - not yet authenticated. authenticated(3) - authenticated. failed(4) - authentication failed. authenticationDisabled(5) - authentication disabled

c3gHdrDrc.name: c3gHdrDrc
c3gHdrDrc.description: High Data Rate (HDR) Data Rate Control (DRC). AT provides requests for data transmissions by sending a Data Rate Control, DRC, message via a specific channel referred to as the DRC channel.

c3gHdrDrcCover.name: c3gHdrDrcCover
c3gHdrDrcCover.description: HDR DRC cover. The DRC cover is a coding applied to identify the sector from which the data is to be transmitted. In one embodiment, the DRC cover is a Walsh code applied to the DRC value, wherein a unique code corresponds to each sector in the Active Set of the AT.

c3gHdrRri.name: c3gHdrRri

c3gCdmaIdentityEntry.name: c3gCdmaIdentityEntry
c3gCdmaIdentityEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the c3gCdmaIdentityTable.

c3gEsn.name: c3gEsn
c3gEsn.description: This object indicates Electronic Serial Number (ESN).

c3gCdmaRoamingPreference.name: c3gCdmaRoamingPreference
c3gCdmaRoamingPreference.description: This object indicates the roaming preference: unknown(1) - preference unknown home(2) - home networks only affiliated(3) - roaming on affiliated networks any(4) - roaming on any network

c3gMdn.name: c3gMdn
c3gMdn.description: Mobile Directory Number (MDN), a dialable number assigned to a wireless phone.

c3gMsid.name: c3gMsid
c3gMsid.description: Mobile Station Identifier (MSID), MSID is utilized to distinguish the mobile station being programmed from other mobile stations during messaging and paging processes, including the downloading of programming information to the mobile station.

c3gCdmaNetworkEntry.name: c3gCdmaNetworkEntry
c3gCdmaNetworkEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the c3gCdmaNetworkTable.

c3gCdmaHybridModePreference.name: c3gCdmaHybridModePreference
c3gCdmaHybridModePreference.description: This object indicates the hybrid mode preference: unknown(1) - preference unknown hybrid(2) - connect to EV-DO/1xRTT services evDoOnly(3) - connect to only EV-DO service oneXRttOnly(4) - connect to only 1xRTT service

c3gCdmaCurrentRoamingStatus.name: c3gCdmaCurrentRoamingStatus
c3gCdmaCurrentRoamingStatus.description: Current 1xRTT roaming status, roaming is a general term in wireless telecommunications that refers to the extending of connectivity service in a location that is different from the home location where the service was registered: unknown(1) - roaming status is unknown. home(2) - connectivity service in home location. roamingWithSid(3) - roaming with SID. roamingWithoutSid(4) - roaming without SID

c3gCurrentIdleDigitalMode.name: c3gCurrentIdleDigitalMode
c3gCurrentIdleDigitalMode.description: Current idle digital mode: unknown(1) - service is unknown noService(2) - no service amps(3) - Advanced Mobile Phone Service (AMPS) cdma(4) - Code Division Multiple Access (CDMA) gsm(5) - Global System for Mobile communications (GSM) hdr(6) - High Data Rate (HDR) wcdma(7) - Wideband Code-Division Multiple-Access (WCDMA) gps(8) - Global Positioning System (GPS) lte(9) - Long Term Evolution (LTE)

c3gCurrentSid.name: c3gCurrentSid
c3gCurrentSid.description: Current System Identifier (SID), SID is a 15-bit numeric identifiers used by cellular systems to identify the home system of a cellular telephone and by the cellular telephone to determine its roaming status. Value of '-1' indicates SID is 'Not Applicable'.

c3gCurrentNid.name: c3gCurrentNid
c3gCurrentNid.description: Current Network Identification (NID), NID is a 16-bit numeric identifiers used by cellular systems. Value of '-1' indicates NID is 'Not Applicable'.

c3gCurrentCallSetupMode.name: c3gCurrentCallSetupMode
c3gCurrentCallSetupMode.description: Current call setup mode. The 1xEV-DO system supports packet data connections to a public or private data network using either mobile IP or simple IP protocol. For simple IP protocol, moving from the coverage area of one PDSN to another PDSN constitutes a change in packet data session. For mobile IP protocol, a packet data session can span several PDSNs as long as the user continuously maintains mobility bindings at the Home Agent (the IP address is persistent). The modes are: unknown(1) - mode is unknown simpleIpOnly(2) - simple IP only mobileIpPreferWithSipFallback(3) - prefer mobile IP with simple IP as fallback mode mobileIpOnly(4) - mobile IP only

c3gServingBaseStationLongitude.name: c3gServingBaseStationLongitude
c3gServingBaseStationLongitude.description: Longitude of the serving base station.

c3gServingBaseStationLatitude.name: c3gServingBaseStationLatitude
c3gServingBaseStationLatitude.description: Latitude of the serving base station.

c3gCdmaProfileCommonEntry.name: c3gCdmaProfileCommonEntry
c3gCdmaProfileCommonEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the c3gCdmaProfileCommonTable.

c3gNumberOfDataProfileConfigurable.name: c3gNumberOfDataProfileConfigurable
c3gNumberOfDataProfileConfigurable.description: The number of data profiles configurable.

c3gCdmaProfileEntry.name: c3gCdmaProfileEntry
c3gCdmaProfileEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the c3gCdmaProfileTable.

c3gCdmaProfileIndex.name: c3gCdmaProfileIndex
c3gCdmaProfileIndex.description: Profile index, combined with entPhysicalIndex to access the profile table c3gCdmaProfileTable.

c3gNai.name: c3gNai
c3gNai.description: Network Access Identifier (NAI). NAI is required to identify the mobile user and the network the mobile user intended to access. The NAI is provided by the mobile node to the dialed ISP during PPP authentication.

c3gAaaPassword.name: c3gAaaPassword
c3gAaaPassword.description: This object indicates the password for AAA.

c3gMnHaSs.name: c3gMnHaSs
c3gMnHaSs.description: Mobile Node (MN) Home Agent (HA) Shared Secret (SS) setting: set(1) - shared secret is set notSet(2) - shared secret is not set

c3gMnHaSpi.name: c3gMnHaSpi
c3gMnHaSpi.description: Mobile Node (MN) Home Agent (HA) Security Parameter Index (SPI).

c3gMnAaaSs.name: c3gMnAaaSs
c3gMnAaaSs.description: Mobile Node (MN) Authentication Authorization Accounting (AAA) Shared Secret (SS) setting: set(1) - shared secret is set notSet(2) - shared secret is not set

c3gMnAaaSpi.name: c3gMnAaaSpi
c3gMnAaaSpi.description: Mobile Node (MN) Authentication Authorization Accounting (AAA) Security Parameter Index (SPI).

c3gHomeAddrType.name: c3gHomeAddrType
c3gHomeAddrType.description: A value that represents the type of the IP Address stored in the object c3gHomeAddr.

c3gHomeAddr.name: c3gHomeAddr
c3gHomeAddr.description: A unicast routable address assigned to a Mobile Node, used as the permanent address of the Mobile Node.

c3gPriHaAddrType.name: c3gPriHaAddrType
c3gPriHaAddrType.description: A value that represents the type of the IP Address stored in the object c3gPriHaAddr.

c3gSecHaAddrType.name: c3gSecHaAddrType
c3gSecHaAddrType.description: A value that represents the type of the IP Address stored in the object c3gSecHaAddr.

c3gCdma1xRttRadioEntry.name: c3gCdma1xRttRadioEntry
c3gCdma1xRttRadioEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the c3gCdma1xRttRadioTable.

c3gCurrent1xRttChannelNumber.name: c3gCurrent1xRttChannelNumber
c3gCurrent1xRttChannelNumber.description: Current 1xRTT channel number. Current channel number to which the modem is attached to the base station. Value of '-1' indicates 'No Service'.

c3gCurrent1xRttChannelState.name: c3gCurrent1xRttChannelState
c3gCurrent1xRttChannelState.description: Current 1xRTT channel state. Indicates whether the modem is scanning or has acquired the channel.

c3gCdma1xRttBandClassTable.name: c3gCdma1xRttBandClassTable
c3gCdma1xRttBandClassTable.description: Cellular 3G CDMA 1xRTT band class table. This table contains band class information for each available band.

c3gCdma1xRttBandClassEntry.name: c3gCdma1xRttBandClassEntry
c3gCdma1xRttBandClassEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the c3gCdma1xRttBandClassTable.

c3gBandClassIndex.name: c3gBandClassIndex
c3gBandClassIndex.description: Band class index, combined with entPhysicalIndex to access the band class table.

c3gCdmaEvDoRadioEntry.name: c3gCdmaEvDoRadioEntry
c3gCdmaEvDoRadioEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the c3gCdmaEvDoRadioTable.

c3gCurrentEvDoChannelNumber.name: c3gCurrentEvDoChannelNumber
c3gCurrentEvDoChannelNumber.description: Current EV-DO channel number. Current channel number to which the modem is attached to the base station. Value of '-1' indicates 'No Service'.

c3gSectorId.name: c3gSectorId
c3gSectorId.description: Sector ID of the base station to which the modem is attached.

c3gSubnetMask.name: c3gSubnetMask
c3gSubnetMask.description: Subnet mask of the sector, not to be confused with the IP subnet mask.

c3gPnOffset.name: c3gPnOffset
c3gPnOffset.description: PN offset. PN offset is a time offset from the beginning of the well-known pseudo-random noise sequence that is used to spread the signal from the base station.

c3gRxMainGainControl.name: c3gRxMainGainControl
c3gRxMainGainControl.description: Received main gain control for the modem. value of '-1' indicates the received main gain control is unavailable.

c3gRxDiversityGainControl.name: c3gRxDiversityGainControl
c3gRxDiversityGainControl.description: Received diversity for the modem. value of '-1' indicates the received diversity is unavailable.

c3gCarrierToInterferenceRatio.name: c3gCarrierToInterferenceRatio
c3gCarrierToInterferenceRatio.description: Carrier to interference ratio. Carrier-to-Interference ratio (C/I) is the ratio of power in an RF carrier to the interference power in the channel.

c3gCdmaEvDoBandClassTable.name: c3gCdmaEvDoBandClassTable
c3gCdmaEvDoBandClassTable.description: Cellular 3G CDMA EV-DO band class table. This table contains band class information for each available band.

c3gCdmaEvDoBandClassEntry.name: c3gCdmaEvDoBandClassEntry
c3gCdmaEvDoBandClassEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the c3gCdmaEvDoBandClassTable.

c3gEvDoBandClass.name: c3gEvDoBandClass
c3gEvDoBandClass.description: This object contains EV-DO band class.

c3gCdmaHistoryTable.name: c3gCdmaHistoryTable
c3gCdmaHistoryTable.description: Cellular 3G CDMA history table. The history of RSSI are carried in an octet of string. Each octet in the octet string has a value from 0 to 150 and the 255 value is reserved to indicate an uninitialized (Invalid) value. The format of the octet string with n octets is as following: [ octet 0 is latest, octet 1 is latest-1, . . octet n-2 is oldest-1, octet n-1 is oldest ] To convert the provided value into dBm the following formula should be used: dBm = (-1)*value;

c3gCdmaHistoryEntry.name: c3gCdmaHistoryEntry
c3gCdmaHistoryEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the c3gCdmaHistoryTable.

c3gCdmaHistory1xRttRssiPerSecond.name: c3gCdmaHistory1xRttRssiPerSecond
c3gCdmaHistory1xRttRssiPerSecond.description: Per-second 1xRTT RSSI history. This object contains a per-second history of 1xRTT RSSI values for the last 60 seconds.

c3gCdmaHistory1xRttRssiPerMinute.name: c3gCdmaHistory1xRttRssiPerMinute
c3gCdmaHistory1xRttRssiPerMinute.description: Per-minute 1xRTT weakest RSSI value history. This object contains a per-minute history of 1xRTT weakest RSSI values for the last 60 minutes. The octet in the string is the weakest RSSI value measured in a minute interval.

c3gCdmaHistory1xRttRssiPerHour.name: c3gCdmaHistory1xRttRssiPerHour
c3gCdmaHistory1xRttRssiPerHour.description: Per-hour 1xRTT weakest RSSI value history. This object contains a per-hour history of 1xRTT weakest RSSI values for the last 72 hours. The octet in the string is the weakest RSSI value measured in an hour interval.

c3gCdmaHistoryEvDoRssiPerSecond.name: c3gCdmaHistoryEvDoRssiPerSecond
c3gCdmaHistoryEvDoRssiPerSecond.description: Per-second EV-DO RSSI history. This object contains a per-second history of EV-DO RSSI values for the last 60 seconds.

c3gCdmaHistoryEvDoRssiPerMinute.name: c3gCdmaHistoryEvDoRssiPerMinute
c3gCdmaHistoryEvDoRssiPerMinute.description: Per-minute EV-DO weakest RSSI value history. This object contains a per-minute history of EV-DO weakest RSSI values for the last 60 minutes. The octet in the string is the weakest RSSI value measured in a minute interval.

c3gCdmaHistoryEvDoRssiPerHour.name: c3gCdmaHistoryEvDoRssiPerHour
c3gCdmaHistoryEvDoRssiPerHour.description: Per-hour EV-DO weakest RSSI value history. This object contains a per-hour history of EV-DO weakest RSSI values for the last 72 hours. The octet in the string is the weakest RSSI value measured in an hour interval.

c3gCdmaSecurityEntry.name: c3gCdmaSecurityEntry
c3gCdmaSecurityEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the c3gCdmaSecurityTable.

c3gCdmaPinSecurityStatus.name: c3gCdmaPinSecurityStatus
c3gCdmaPinSecurityStatus.description: CDMA Personal Identification Number (PIN) security: unknown(1) - PIN security unknown locked(2) - PIN security is locked unlocked(3) - PIN security is unlocked

c3gCdmaPowerUpLockStatus.name: c3gCdmaPowerUpLockStatus
c3gCdmaPowerUpLockStatus.description: CDMA power up lock: unknown(1) - power up lock unknown enabled(2) - power up lock enabled disabled(3) - power up lock disabled

c3gGsmIdentityEntry.name: c3gGsmIdentityEntry
c3gGsmIdentityEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the c3gGsmIdentityTable.

c3gImsi.name: c3gImsi
c3gImsi.description: International Mobile Subscriber Identifier (IMSI), a unique 15-digit code used to identify an individual user on a GSM/LTE network.

c3gImei.name: c3gImei
c3gImei.description: International Mobile Equipment Identifier (IMEI), a unique 15 or 17 digit code used to identify an individual mobile station to a GSM, UMTS or LTE network.

c3gIccId.name: c3gIccId
c3gIccId.description: This object indicates the Integrated Circuit Card ID (ICCID). The ICCID is defined by the ITU-T recommendation E.118. ICCIDs are stored in the SIM cards and are also engraved or printed on the SIM card body during a process called personalization.

c3gMsisdn.name: c3gMsisdn
c3gMsisdn.description: This object indicates the Mobile Subscriber Integrated Services Digital Network Number (MSISDN). It is a number uniquely identifying a subscription in a GSM, UMTS or LTE mobile network. It represents the telephone number to the SIM card in a mobile/cellular phone.

c3gFsn.name: c3gFsn
c3gFsn.description: Forward Sequence Number (FSN), a message acknowledgement method using sequence number in the forward direction.

c3gModemStatus.name: c3gModemStatus
c3gModemStatus.description: Modem status: unknown(1) - modem status is unknown offLine(2) - modem is off line onLine(3) - modem is on line lowPowerMode(4) - modem is in the low power mode

c3gGsmRoamingPreference.name: c3gGsmRoamingPreference
c3gGsmRoamingPreference.description: This object indicates the roaming preference.

c3gGsmNetworkTable.name: c3gGsmNetworkTable
c3gGsmNetworkTable.description: Cellular GSM Network table. This table is applicable in both 3G and 4G-LTE technology mode

c3gGsmNetworkEntry.name: c3gGsmNetworkEntry
c3gGsmNetworkEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the c3gGsmNetworkTable.

c3gGsmLac.name: c3gGsmLac
c3gGsmLac.description: Location Area Code (LAC), also called as Tracking Area Code (TAC) in LTE standard. LAC/TAC is given by the base station.

c3gGsmCurrentServiceStatus.name: c3gGsmCurrentServiceStatus
c3gGsmCurrentServiceStatus.description: Current Service Status: unknown(1) - current service status is unknown noService(2) - no service normal(3) - service status is normal emergencyOnly(4) - emergency service only

c3gGsmCurrentServiceError.name: c3gGsmCurrentServiceError
c3gGsmCurrentServiceError.description: Current service error: unknown(1) - Unknown none(2) - None imsiUnknownInHlr(3) - IMSI unknown in HLR (Home Location Register) illegalMs(4) - Illegal MS (Mobile Station) imsiUnknownInVlr(5) - IMSI unknown in VLR (Visitor Location Register) imeiNotAccepted(6) - IMEI not accepted illegalMe(7) - Illegal ME (Mobile Entity) gprsServNotAllowed(8) - GPRS services not allowed gprsNonGprsServNotAllow(9) - GPRS and non-GPRS services not allowed msIdentUnknown(10) - MS identity unknown implicitlyDetached(11) - Implicitly detached plmnNotAllowed(12) - PLMN not allowed lacNotAllowed(13) - LAC not allowed roamingNotAllowed(14) - Roaming not allowed gprsServNotAllowInPlmn(15) - GPRS services not allowed in this PLMN noSuitableCellInLa(16) - No suitable cells in LA (Location Area) mscTempNotReachable(17) - MSC (Mobile Switching Center) temporarily not reachable networkFailure(18) - Network failure macFailure(19) - MAC failure synchFailure(20) - Synch failure congestion(21) - Congestion gsmAuthenNotAccept(22) - GSM/LTE Authentication not accepted servOptionNotSupport(23) - Service option not supported reqServOptionNotSub(24) - Requested service option not subscribed servOptionOutOfOrder(25) - Service option out of order callCannotIdentified(26) - Call cannot be identified noPdpContextActivated(27) - No PDP context activated invalidMandatInfo(28) - Invalid mandatory info unpsecProtErr(29) - Unspecified protocol error

c3gGsmCurrentService.name: c3gGsmCurrentService
c3gGsmCurrentService.description: Current service type: unknown(1) - service type is unknown invalid(2) - no service circuitSwitched(3) - circuit switched service packetSwitched(4) - packet switched service combined(5) - combination of circuit and packet switched service

c3gGsmPacketService.name: c3gGsmPacketService
c3gGsmPacketService.description: Packet Service type: unknown(1) - service type is unknown. none(2) - no service. gprs(3) - General Packet Radio Service (GPRS). edge(4) - Enhanced Data rates for GSM Evolution (EDGE). umtsWcdma(5) - Universal Mobile Telecommunications System (UMTS) / Wideband Code-Division Multiple-Access (W-CDMA). hsdpa(6) - High-Speed Downlink Packet Access (HSDPA) hsdpa(7) - High-Speed Uplink Packet Access (HSUPA) hspa(8) - High-Speed Packet Access (HSPA) hspaPlus(9) - High-Speed Packet Access (HSPA) Plus lte(10) - Long Term Evolution

c3gGsmCurrentRoamingStatus.name: c3gGsmCurrentRoamingStatus
c3gGsmCurrentRoamingStatus.description: This object indicates whether the modem is in the home network or is roaming.

c3gGsmNetworkSelectionMode.name: c3gGsmNetworkSelectionMode
c3gGsmNetworkSelectionMode.description: Network selection mode. Can be manual selection mode or automatic selection mode. Set to automatic by default.

c3gGsmCountry.name: c3gGsmCountry
c3gGsmCountry.description: Country code. Country code string is given by the base station.

c3gGsmNetwork.name: c3gGsmNetwork
c3gGsmNetwork.description: Network code. Network Code string is given by the base station.

c3gGsmMcc.name: c3gGsmMcc
c3gGsmMcc.description: Mobile Country Code (MCC). Value of '-1' indicates MCC is 'Not Applicable'.

c3gGsmMnc.name: c3gGsmMnc
c3gGsmMnc.description: Mobile Network Code (MNC). Value of '-1' indicates MNC is 'Not Applicable'.

c3gGsmRac.name: c3gGsmRac
c3gGsmRac.description: Routing Area Code (RAC). RAC is given by the base station.

c3gGsmCurrentCellId.name: c3gGsmCurrentCellId
c3gGsmCurrentCellId.description: Cell Identifier of current cell. Cell ID is given by the base station.

c3gGsmCurrentPrimaryScramblingCode.name: c3gGsmCurrentPrimaryScramblingCode
c3gGsmCurrentPrimaryScramblingCode.description: Primary scrambling code of current cell. The primary scrambling code is typically identified through symbol-by-symbol correlation over the CPICH (Common Pilot Channel) with all codes within the code group, after the primary scrambling code has been identified, the Primary CCPCH can be detected and the system and cell specific BCH information can be read.

c3gGsmPlmnSelection.name: c3gGsmPlmnSelection
c3gGsmPlmnSelection.description: Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) selection. Can be manual selection mode or automatic selection mode. Set to automatic by default.

c3gGsmTotalByteTransmitted.name: c3gGsmTotalByteTransmitted
c3gGsmTotalByteTransmitted.description: Total number of bytes transmitted for all calls. It is the total number of bytes transmitted by modem, not to be confused with the number of bytes transmitted through the interface.

c3gGsmTotalByteReceived.name: c3gGsmTotalByteReceived
c3gGsmTotalByteReceived.description: Total number of bytes received for all calls. It is the total number of bytes received by modem, not to be confused with the number of bytes received from the interface.

c3gGsmPdpProfileTable.name: c3gGsmPdpProfileTable
c3gGsmPdpProfileTable.description: Cellular GSM PDP profiles table. Cellular device contains multiple profile entries which can be used to establish cellular data connections (PDP contexts). Users can choose any of available PDP profiles to establish data connections. Data connections are described in c3gGsmPacketSessionTable. This table is applicable in only 3G technology mode. Refer CISCO-WAN-CELL-EXT-MIB when in 4G-LTE mode.

c3gGsmPdpProfileEntry.name: c3gGsmPdpProfileEntry
c3gGsmPdpProfileEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the c3gGsmPdpProfileTable.

c3gGsmPdpProfileIndex.name: c3gGsmPdpProfileIndex
c3gGsmPdpProfileIndex.description: Profile index, combined with entPhysicalIndex to access profile table.

c3gGsmPdpProfileType.name: c3gGsmPdpProfileType
c3gGsmPdpProfileType.description: This object indicates configured Packet Data Protocol (PDP) type.

c3gGsmPdpProfileAddr.name: c3gGsmPdpProfileAddr
c3gGsmPdpProfileAddr.description: Configured PDP/EPS Bearer address. PDP type is defined in c3gGsmPdpProfileType.

c3gGsmPdpProfileApn.name: c3gGsmPdpProfileApn
c3gGsmPdpProfileApn.description: This object indicates profile Access Point Name (APN). This information is provided by the service provider.

c3gGsmPdpProfileAuthenType.name: c3gGsmPdpProfileAuthenType
c3gGsmPdpProfileAuthenType.description: This object indicates PDP authentication type supported. CHAP and PAP are supported in GSM. The type of authentication to be used is provided by the service provider.

c3gGsmPdpProfileUsername.name: c3gGsmPdpProfileUsername
c3gGsmPdpProfileUsername.description: This object indicates the username to be used for PDP authentication. This information is provided by the service provider.

c3gGsmPdpProfilePassword.name: c3gGsmPdpProfilePassword
c3gGsmPdpProfilePassword.description: This object indicates the password to be used for PDP authentication. This information is provided by the service provider.

c3gGsmPdpProfileRowStatus.name: c3gGsmPdpProfileRowStatus
c3gGsmPdpProfileRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. This object is used to manage creation, modification and deletion of rows in this table.

c3gGsmPacketSessionTable.name: c3gGsmPacketSessionTable
c3gGsmPacketSessionTable.description: Cellular 3G GSM packet session table. This table is applicable in only 3G technology mode. Refer CISCO-WAN-CELL-EXT-MIB when in 4G-LTE mode.

c3gGsmPacketSessionEntry.name: c3gGsmPacketSessionEntry
c3gGsmPacketSessionEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the c3gGsmPacketSessionTable.

c3gGsmPacketSessionStatus.name: c3gGsmPacketSessionStatus
c3gGsmPacketSessionStatus.description: This object indicates PDP session status of the profile. This is active when the call is established and PDP contextr has become active.

c3gGsmPdpType.name: c3gGsmPdpType
c3gGsmPdpType.description: This object indicates current session PDP type.

c3gGsmPdpAddress.name: c3gGsmPdpAddress
c3gGsmPdpAddress.description: Current session PDP context/EPS Bearer address. PDP type is obtained from c3gGsmPdpType.

c3gGsmReqUmtsQosTable.name: c3gGsmReqUmtsQosTable
c3gGsmReqUmtsQosTable.description: Requested UMTS QoS parameters table. This table contains UMTS QoS parameters requested by modem to the cellular network via PDP Context Activation Request message. The requested UMTS QoS profile is optional. This table is applicable only in 3G technology mode.

c3gGsmReqUmtsQosEntry.name: c3gGsmReqUmtsQosEntry

c3gGsmChannelNumber.description: Channel number to which the modem is attached. This is only applicable in 3G technology mode. Refer CISCO-WAN-CELL-EXT-MIB for the LTE uplink and downlink channel values

c3gGsmNumberOfNearbyCell.name: c3gGsmNumberOfNearbyCell
c3gGsmNumberOfNearbyCell.description: This object indicates the current total number of nearby cell in the c3gGsmNearbyCellTable. User can poll this object to get the total number of nearby cell before polling c3gGsmNearbyCellTable.

c3gGsmNearbyCellTable.name: c3gGsmNearbyCellTable
c3gGsmNearbyCellTable.description: Cellular GSM/4G-LTE nearby cell table. Object c3gGsmNumberOfNearbyCell indicates the total number of nearby cell in this table.

c3gGsmNearbyCellEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the c3gGsmNearbyCellTable.

c3gGsmNearbyCellIndex.description: Nearby cell index, combined with entPhysicalIndex to access the Nearby cell table c3gGsmNearbyCellTable.

c3gGsmNearbyCellRscp.name: c3gGsmNearbyCellRscp
c3gGsmNearbyCellRscp.description: Nearby cell Received Signal Code Power (RSCP).

c3gGsmHistoryTable.name: c3gGsmHistoryTable
c3gGsmHistoryTable.description: Cellular 3G GSM/4G-LTE RSSI history table. The history of RSSI are carried in an octet of string. Each octet in the octet string has a value from 0 to 150 and the 255 value is reserved to indicate an uninitialized (Invalid) value. The format of the octet string with n octets is as following: [ octet 0 is latest, octet 1 is latest-1, . . octet n-2 is oldest-1, octet n-1 is oldest ] To convert the provided value into dBm the following formula should be used: dBm = (-1)*value;

c3gGsmHistoryEntry.name: c3gGsmHistoryEntry
c3gGsmHistoryEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the c3gGsmHistoryTable.

c3gGsmHistoryRssiPerSecond.name: c3gGsmHistoryRssiPerSecond
c3gGsmHistoryRssiPerSecond.description: Per-second RSSI history. This object contains a per-second history of RSSI values for the last 60 seconds.

c3gGsmHistoryRssiPerMinute.name: c3gGsmHistoryRssiPerMinute
c3gGsmHistoryRssiPerMinute.description: Per-minute weakest RSSI value history. This object contains a per-minute history of weakest RSSI values for the last 60 minutes. The octet in the string is the weakest RSSI value measured in a minute interval.

c3gGsmHistoryRssiPerHour.name: c3gGsmHistoryRssiPerHour
c3gGsmHistoryRssiPerHour.description: Per-hour weakest RSSI value history. This object contains a per-hour history of weakest RSSI values for the last 72 hours. The octet in the string is the weakest RSSI value measured in an hour interval.

c3gGsmSecurityEntry.name: c3gGsmSecurityEntry

c3gGsmChv1.description: Card Holder Verification 1 (CHV1), if enabled, the PIN will be verified, if disabled, the PIN will not be verified.

c3gGsmSimStatus.name: c3gGsmSimStatus
c3gGsmSimStatus.description: SIM status. Indicates whether the SIM is present or removed from the SIM socket, and its current status.

c3gGsmSimUserOperationRequired.name: c3gGsmSimUserOperationRequired
c3gGsmSimUserOperationRequired.description: If the SIM is protected (for example, because of CHV1 enabled), it will indicate the type of user operation required.

c3gGsmNumberOfRetriesRemaining.name: c3gGsmNumberOfRetriesRemaining
c3gGsmNumberOfRetriesRemaining.description: Indicates the number of attempts remaining in case the SIM is locked. If the number of retries becomes zero, the SIM is blocked and becomes unusable.

c3gWanLbsCommonTable.name: c3gWanLbsCommonTable
c3gWanLbsCommonTable.description: This table contains information about the Cellular Location Based service feature. This GPS data is provided by the wireless modem upon GPS configuration.

c3gWanLbsCommonEntry.name: c3gWanLbsCommonEntry
c3gWanLbsCommonEntry.description: This entry contains information about the Cellular Location Based service variables returned by the wireless modem.

c3gLbsModeSelected.name: c3gLbsModeSelected
c3gLbsModeSelected.description: Mode of Location base service selected. unKnown - mode selection unkown standAlone - Standalone mode msBased - MS-Based mode msAssist - MS-Assist mode reserved - reserved for future use

c3gLbsState.name: c3gLbsState
c3gLbsState.description: Location base service state. gpsDisabled - GPS is disabled gpsEnabled - GPS is enabled gpsLocError - GPS encounters error gpsAcquiring - GPS is acquiring fix

c3gLbsLocFixError.name: c3gLbsLocFixError
c3gLbsLocFixError.reference: Refer to the following documents for the error code's full definitions. Sierra Wireless CDMA EVDO CnS Reference_1.2.pdf under Location Based Services section.
c3gLbsLocFixError.description: Location base service fix error code.

c3gLbsLocUncertaintyAngle.name: c3gLbsLocUncertaintyAngle
c3gLbsLocUncertaintyAngle.description: GPS Uncertainty parameter Angle, in degrees for the Uncertainty info returned by the GPS device while doing a location fix.

c3gLbsLocUncertaintyA.name: c3gLbsLocUncertaintyA
c3gLbsLocUncertaintyA.description: GPS Uncertainty parameter A, value in meters for the Uncertainty info returned by the GPS device while doing a location fix.

c3gLbsLocUncertaintyPos.name: c3gLbsLocUncertaintyPos
c3gLbsLocUncertaintyPos.description: GPS Uncertainty parameter position, value in meters for the Uncertainty info returned by the GPS device while doing a location fix.

c3gLbsFixtype.name: c3gLbsFixtype
c3gLbsFixtype.description: The type of location fix in Location Base service. none - default case, while LBS is not enabled. twoDimension - 2D location fix. threeDimension - 3D location fix.

c3gLbsHeightValid.name: c3gLbsHeightValid
c3gLbsHeightValid.description: This object indicates whether the height returned by the GPS device is valid during location fix.

c3gLbsHeight.name: c3gLbsHeight
c3gLbsHeight.description: This object indicates the GPS height parameter returned by the GPS device while performing location fix.

c3gLbsLocUncertaintyVertical.name: c3gLbsLocUncertaintyVertical
c3gLbsLocUncertaintyVertical.description: GPS parameter vertical velocity parameter returned by the GPS device while performing location fix.

c3gLbsVelocityValid.name: c3gLbsVelocityValid
c3gLbsVelocityValid.description: This object indicates whether the Velocity value returned by the GPS device is valid.

c3gLbsHeading.name: c3gLbsHeading
c3gLbsHeading.description: The compass direction toward which the GPS receiver is (or should be) moving.

c3gLbsVelocityHorizontal.name: c3gLbsVelocityHorizontal
c3gLbsVelocityHorizontal.description: Horizontal Velocity in meters per second the GPS device is heading. This is the value returned by the GPS satellite relative to the last horizontal location of the GPS device. If at Time X satellite sees the location of GPS device is L1 and then at Time Y satellite sees the location is L2 then speed is (L2 - L1) / ( Y - X).

c3gLbsVelocityVertical.name: c3gLbsVelocityVertical
c3gLbsVelocityVertical.description: Vertical Velocity in meters per second the GPS device is heading. This is the value returned by the GPS satellite relative to the last vertical location of the GPS device. If at Time X satellite sees the location of GPS device is L1 and then at Time Y satellite sees the location is L2 then speed is (L2 - L1) / ( Y - X).

c3gLbsHepe.name: c3gLbsHepe
c3gLbsHepe.description: Horizontal Estimated Position Error returned by the GPS satellite for current position of the GPS device.

c3gLbsNumSatellites.name: c3gLbsNumSatellites
c3gLbsNumSatellites.description: Number of GPS satellites in vision to the modem while GPS tracking is on.

c3gWanLbsSatelliteInfoTable.name: c3gWanLbsSatelliteInfoTable
c3gWanLbsSatelliteInfoTable.description: This table provides information on each satellite that is visible to the modem during the location fix. These satellites guide the device to acquire a 2D or 3D location fix.

c3gWanLbsSatelliteInfoEntry.name: c3gWanLbsSatelliteInfoEntry
c3gWanLbsSatelliteInfoEntry.description: This table provides information about each satellite's elevation, azimuth, Signal to Noise ratio (SNR) and its reference number local to the router.

c3gWanLbsSatelliteInfoIndex.name: c3gWanLbsSatelliteInfoIndex
c3gWanLbsSatelliteInfoIndex.description: An index that is assigned to each satellite under a modem and in combination with entPhysicalIndex uniquely identify it. This index is assigned arbitrarily by the engine and is not saved over reboots.

c3gWanLbsSatelliteNumber.name: c3gWanLbsSatelliteNumber
c3gWanLbsSatelliteNumber.reference: Refer to the following documents for detailed information of Satellites. Sierra Wireless CDMA EVDO CnS Reference_1.2.pdf under Location Based Services section
c3gWanLbsSatelliteNumber.description: Each Satellite is assigned a unique number within this device.This object can be used to locate a particular satellite under a modem.

c3gWanLbsSatelliteElevation.name: c3gWanLbsSatelliteElevation
c3gWanLbsSatelliteElevation.reference: Refer to the following documents for detailed information of Satellites elevation. Sierra Wireless CDMA EVDO CnS Reference_1.2.pdf under Location Based Services section
c3gWanLbsSatelliteElevation.description: Angle of Elevation between the GPS antenna pointing direction, directly towards the satellite, and the local horizontal plane. It is the up-down angle

c3gWanLbsSatelliteAzimuth.name: c3gWanLbsSatelliteAzimuth
c3gWanLbsSatelliteAzimuth.reference: Refer to the following documents for detailed information of Satellites Azimuth. Sierra Wireless CDMA EVDO CnS Reference_1.2.pdf under Location Based Services section
c3gWanLbsSatelliteAzimuth.description: Azimuth of the current satellite in context referenced by the Satellite InfoIndex. Azimuth is the degree of rotation of the satellites dish on its vertical plane.

c3gWanLbsSatelliteInfoSignalNoiseRatio.name: c3gWanLbsSatelliteInfoSignalNoiseRatio
c3gWanLbsSatelliteInfoSignalNoiseRatio.reference: Refer to the following documents for detailed information of signal to noise ration in LBS. Sierra Wireless CDMA EVDO CnS Reference_1.2.pdf under Location Based Services section
c3gWanLbsSatelliteInfoSignalNoiseRatio.description: Signal to Noise Ratio(SNR) of received GPS signal. SNR is refered to as the signal strength in GPS standards.

c3gWanLbsSatelliteUsed.name: c3gWanLbsSatelliteUsed
c3gWanLbsSatelliteUsed.description: Is this satellite in line of sight to the modem used in calculating the GPS location?

c3gWanLbsSatelliteInfoRowStatus.name: c3gWanLbsSatelliteInfoRowStatus
c3gWanLbsSatelliteInfoRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. This object is used to manage creation, modification and deletion of rows in this table.

c3gSmsCommonTable.name: c3gSmsCommonTable
c3gSmsCommonTable.description: This table contains Cellular SMS management MIB objects.

c3gSmsCommonEntry.name: c3gSmsCommonEntry
c3gSmsCommonEntry.description: An entry contains counters for the SMS messages received, placed, errored and archived on CDMA, GSM or LTE based modems.

c3gSmsServiceAvailable.name: c3gSmsServiceAvailable
c3gSmsServiceAvailable.description: This object indicates the availability of SMS Service.

c3gSmsOutSmsCount.name: c3gSmsOutSmsCount
c3gSmsOutSmsCount.description: Number of SMS messages which have been sent successfully.

c3gSmsOutSmsErrorCount.name: c3gSmsOutSmsErrorCount
c3gSmsOutSmsErrorCount.description: Number of SMS message that could not be sent.

c3gSmsInSmsStorageUsed.name: c3gSmsInSmsStorageUsed
c3gSmsInSmsStorageUsed.description: Number of SMS message records space used in the Incoming SMS message storage. One standard SMS message (cdma or gsm) occupies 1 unit of record storage space. A big SMS message can span 'n' sms record space but still be called as 1 SMS message. Storage used can be greater than or equal to total number of Incoming SMS received.

c3gSmsInSmsStorageUnused.name: c3gSmsInSmsStorageUnused
c3gSmsInSmsStorageUnused.description: The number of SMS messages record space left unused in the Incoming SMS message storage. This is equal to c3gSmsInSmsStorageMax - c3gSmsInSmsStorageUsed.

c3gSmsInSmsArchiveCount.name: c3gSmsInSmsArchiveCount
c3gSmsInSmsArchiveCount.description: Number of successful archive of Incoming SMS messages since router reload. Each SMS message occupies x bytes of space. So if the incoming message is huge, then it is archived as multiple of x bytes but still called as one SMS message. This is the difference between c3gSmsInSmsArchiveCount and c3gSmsInSmsArchived.

c3gSmsInSmsArchiveErrorCount.name: c3gSmsInSmsArchiveErrorCount
c3gSmsInSmsArchiveErrorCount.description: The number of Incoming SMS messages that could not be archived since device was reloaded.

c3gSmsArchiveUrl.name: c3gSmsArchiveUrl
c3gSmsArchiveUrl.description: URL of the sms archive directory on the ftp server. The url will be of this format ftp://x.y.z.k/user/dirname

c3gSmsOutSmsStatus.name: c3gSmsOutSmsStatus
c3gSmsOutSmsStatus.description: Status of the last send operation of outgoing SMS message to the network.

c3gSmsInSmsCount.name: c3gSmsInSmsCount
c3gSmsInSmsCount.description: Number of SMS messages which have been received successfully and stored in router. These SMS's are a mirror copy of SMS stored in Modem or SIM

c3gSmsInSmsDeleted.name: c3gSmsInSmsDeleted
c3gSmsInSmsDeleted.description: Number of SMS messages which have been deleted since router boot up. This does not include SMS messages that are already archived.

c3gSmsInSmsStorageMax.name: c3gSmsInSmsStorageMax
c3gSmsInSmsStorageMax.description: Number of SMS message records space allocated in the router's DRAM to store Incoming SMS messages.

c3gSmsInSmsCallBack.name: c3gSmsInSmsCallBack
c3gSmsInSmsCallBack.description: Number of incoming SMS messages that triggered callback.

c3gSmsOutSmsPendingCount.name: c3gSmsOutSmsPendingCount
c3gSmsOutSmsPendingCount.description: Number of outgoing SMS messages that are in pending queue of the router.

c3gSmsOutSmsArchiveCount.name: c3gSmsOutSmsArchiveCount
c3gSmsOutSmsArchiveCount.description: Number of successfull archive of outgoing SMS messages since router reload.

c3gSmsOutSmsArchiveErrorCount.name: c3gSmsOutSmsArchiveErrorCount
c3gSmsOutSmsArchiveErrorCount.description: Number of failed archive of outgoing SMS messages since router reload.

c3gSmsInSmsArchived.name: c3gSmsInSmsArchived
c3gSmsInSmsArchived.description: Number of Incoming SMS messages that are successfully archived since router reload.

c3gModemUpNotif.name: c3gModemUpNotif
